<p class="EnTeteTranscription">McKenzie, Alexander. Journal of Great Bear Lake, 1805-1806. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0006</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">July 12<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">on a River Supposed to be 3 or 4 Miles Broad where there is a great Quantity of Beaver<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>his is the Large River Sir Alexander was informed of when on his voyage in this quarter<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I expect in two or three years to have people sent there if possible.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>raded a few skins with the Indians of Bluefish River.  Completed 12 packs<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 13<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 11 O Clock and Encamped 10 miles below Bear River<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 14<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 5 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>t 9 O Clock put a shore to Breakfas at the Enterence of Great Bear River<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Encamped at 7 O Clock at Rappid Island<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 15<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 5 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[P]</span>assed <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Isle que debule</span> at 1 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  S wind<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Encamped 8 miles above Castore que debule at 8 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 16<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 3 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[E]</span>ncamped at 10 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Rain<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 17<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 2 O Clock in the afternoon<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Clear weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>t 6 O Clock arrived at 3 Camps or Lodges of Dogrib Indians<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey had some provisions about a days march in land but although our pemegan was hardily eatible I would not remain to send for it<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Encamped at 8 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 18<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 4 O Clock and Encamped oposite the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Gro Roshe</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 19<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 4 O Clock and Encamped 9 miles below Rivers <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Sole</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[July]</span> 20<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked a 5 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>t 8 O Clock put on shore to Breakfast at 5 Lodges of Dog Rib Indians of the Forks<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey have been called Beaver Indians by some in this Countrie but they are Dog Rib (or Slaves)<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>heir intentions was to go and join those of the same Nation at Great Bear Lake.  I desired that they would return to their Fort that any Indians that left their Fort would not receive a pipe of Tobbaccoe at any other Fort<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey promised not to go further down and as soon as the Leaves was yellow they would return to the Forks, (or Fort)<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I embarked after giving them each two Inches of Tobbaccoe and Camped 16 miles below Rockey Mountain Fort.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">21<sup>st</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 5 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[P]</span>assed Rockey Mountain Fort at 11 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Encamped at 8 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he pemegan was so bad I gave the men a dram and some sugar to mix with their pemegan<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he most of them got sick &amp; weak having</p>
